amns_data.name: amns_data
amns_data.description: Atomic, molecular, nuclear and surface physics data. Each occurrence contains the data for a given element (nuclear charge), describing various physical processes. For each process, data tables are organized by charge states. The coordinate system used by the data tables is described under the coordinate_system node.

balance_of_plant.name: balance_of_plant
balance_of_plant.description: Electrical and thermal power balance of the plant

barometry.name: barometry
barometry.description: Pressure measurements in the vacuum vessel. NB will need to change the type of the pressure node to signal_1d when moving to the new LL.

b_field_non_axisymmetric.name: b_field_non_axisymmetric
b_field_non_axisymmetric.description: Vacuum 3d error magnetic field (the full 3d magnetic field with the axisymmetric components subtracted)

breeding_blanket.name: breeding_blanket
breeding_blanket.description: Description of the breeding blanket and neutron shield (if any, the shield is considered as an additional layer of a given blanket module)

bremsstrahlung_visible.name: bremsstrahlung_visible
bremsstrahlung_visible.description: Diagnostic for measuring the bremsstrahlung from thermal particules in the visible light range, in view of determining the effective charge of the plasma.

calorimetry.name: calorimetry
calorimetry.description: Calometry measurements on various tokamak subsystems

camera_ir.name: camera_ir
camera_ir.description: Infrared camera for monitoring of Plasma Facing Components

camera_visible.name: camera_visible
camera_visible.description: Camera in the visible light range

camera_x_rays.name: camera_x_rays
camera_x_rays.description: X-rays imaging camera (can be used for soft or hard X-rays imaging systems)

coils_non_axisymmetric.name: coils_non_axisymmetric
coils_non_axisymmetric.description: Non axisymmetric active coils system (e.g. ELM control coils, error field correction coils, ...)

core_instant_changes.name: core_instant_changes
core_instant_changes.description: Instant changes of the radial core plasma profiles due to pellet, MHD, ...

core_sources.name: core_sources
core_sources.description: Core plasma thermal source terms (for the transport equations of the thermal species). Energy terms correspond to the full kinetic energy equation (i.e. the energy flux takes into account the energy transported by the particle flux)

core_transport.name: core_transport
core_transport.description: Core plasma transport of particles, energy, momentum and poloidal flux. The transport of particles, energy and momentum is described by diffusion coefficients, D, and convection velocities, v. These are defined by the total fluxes of particles, energy and momentum, across a flux surface given by : V' [-D Y' <|grad(rho_tor_norm)|^2> + v Y <|grad(rho_tor_norm)|>], where Y represents the particles, energy and momentum density, respectively, while V is the volume inside a flux surface, the primes denote derivatives with respect to rho_tor_norm and < X > is the flux surface average of a quantity X. This formulation remains valid when changing simultaneously rho_tor_norm into rho_tor in the gradient terms and in the derivatives denoted by the prime. The average flux stored in the IDS as sibling of D and v is the total flux described above divided by the flux surface area V' <|grad(rho_tor_norm)|>. Note that the energy flux includes the energy transported by the particle flux, in this form: Q =  V' [- n D (T)' <|grad(rho_tor_norm)|^2> + v (nT) <|grad(rho_tor_norm)|>] + flux_multiplier * T * particle_flux

cryostat.name: cryostat
cryostat.description: Description of the cryostat surrounding the machine (if any)

dataset_fair.name: dataset_fair
dataset_fair.description: FAIR metadata related to the dataset, providing inforrmation on licensing, annotations, references using this dataset, versioning and validity, provenance. This IDS is using Dublin Core metadata standard whenever possible

disruption.name: disruption
disruption.description: Description of physics quantities of specific interest during a disruption, in particular halo currents, etc ...

distribution_sources.name: distribution_sources
distribution_sources.description: Sources of particles for input to kinetic equations, e.g. Fokker-Planck calculation. The sources could originate from e.g. NBI or fusion reactions.

distributions.name: distributions
distributions.description: Distribution function(s) of one or many particle species. This structure is specifically designed to handle non-Maxwellian distribution function generated during heating and current drive, typically solved using a Fokker-Planck calculation perturbed by a heating scheme (e.g. IC, EC, LH, NBI, or alpha heating) and then relaxed by Coloumb collisions.

ec_launchers.name: ec_launchers
ec_launchers.description: Launchers for heating and current drive in the electron cyclotron (EC) frequencies.

edge_profiles.name: edge_profiles
edge_profiles.description: Edge plasma profiles (includes the scrape-off layer and possibly part of the confined plasma)

edge_sources.name: edge_sources
edge_sources.description: Edge plasma sources. Energy terms correspond to the full kinetic energy equation (i.e. the energy flux takes into account the energy transported by the particle flux)

edge_transport.name: edge_transport
edge_transport.description: Edge plasma transport. Energy terms correspond to the full kinetic energy equation (i.e. the energy flux takes into account the energy transported by the particle flux)

em_coupling.name: em_coupling
em_coupling.description: Description of the axisymmetric mutual electromagnetics; does not include non-axisymmetric coil systems; the convention is Quantity_Sensor_Source

equilibrium.name: equilibrium
equilibrium.description: Description of a 2D, axi-symmetric, tokamak equilibrium; result of an equilibrium code.

ferritic.name: ferritic
ferritic.description: Description of ferritic material (inserts, TBMs, NBI shielding, welds, rebar, etc...)

gas_injection.name: gas_injection
gas_injection.description: Gas injection by a system of pipes and valves

gas_pumping.name: gas_pumping
gas_pumping.description: Gas pumping by a set of ducts

gyrokinetics_local.name: gyrokinetics_local
gyrokinetics_local.description: Description of a local gyrokinetic simulation (delta-f, flux-tube). All quantities within this IDS are normalized (apart from time and from the normalizing quantities structure), thus independent of rhostar, consistently with the local approximation and a spectral representation is assumed in the perpendicular plane (i.e. homogeneous turbulence).

ic_antennas.name: ic_antennas
ic_antennas.description: Antenna systems for heating and current drive in the ion cyclotron (IC) frequencies.

lh_antennas.name: lh_antennas
lh_antennas.description: Antenna systems for heating and current drive in the Lower Hybrid (LH) frequencies. In the definitions below, the front (or mouth) of the antenna refers to the plasma facing side of the antenna, while the back refers to the waveguides connected side of the antenna (towards the RF generators).

magnetics.name: magnetics
magnetics.description: Magnetic diagnostics for equilibrium identification and plasma shape control.

operational_instrumentation.name: operational_instrumentation
operational_instrumentation.description: Diagnostics measuring mechanical displacement, acceleration or strains on various parts of the device

mhd.name: mhd
mhd.description: Magnetohydrodynamic activity, description of perturbed fields and profiles using the Generic Grid Description.

nbi.name: nbi
nbi.description: Neutral Beam Injection systems and description of the fast neutrals that arrive into the torus

pellets.name: pellets
pellets.description: Description of pellets launched into the plasma

pf_active.name: pf_active
pf_active.description: Description of the axisymmetric active poloidal field (PF) coils and supplies; includes the limits of these systems; includes the forces on them; does not include non-axisymmetric coil systems

pf_passive.name: pf_passive
pf_passive.description: Description of the axisymmetric passive conductors, currents flowing in them. Electromagnetic simulations are expected to use only this IDS to describe passive conductors and their specific discretization, not the component-related IDS (e.g. wall) which are used to store e.g. the component machine description

pf_plasma.name: pf_plasma
pf_plasma.description: Description of the axisymmetric currents flowing in the plasma, to be used in circuit equations, represented by a set of elements

plasma_initiation.name: plasma_initiation
plasma_initiation.description: Description the early phases of the plasma, before an equilibrium can be calculated

plasma_profiles.name: plasma_profiles
plasma_profiles.description: Plasma profiles (core and/or edge). This IDS is a prototype based on the merge of core_profiles, edge_profiles and the MHD IDS, for testing purposes only at this stage. It contains magnetic field maps to describe magnetic field fluctuations, while the equilibrium magnetic field is described in the equilibrium IDS

plasma_sources.name: plasma_sources
plasma_sources.description: Plasma sources. This IDS is a prototype based on the merge of core_sources and edge_sources. Energy terms correspond to the full kinetic energy equation (i.e. the energy flux takes into account the energy transported by the particle flux)

plasma_transport.name: plasma_transport
plasma_transport.description: Plasma transport. This IDS is a prototype based on the merge of core_transport and edge_transport. Energy terms correspond to the full kinetic energy equation (i.e. the energy flux takes into account the energy transported by the particle flux)

pulse_schedule.name: pulse_schedule
pulse_schedule.description: Description of Pulse Schedule, described by subsystems waveform references and an enveloppe around them. The controllers, pulse schedule and SDN are defined in separate IDSs. All names and identifiers of subsystems appearing in the pulse_schedule must be identical to those used in the IDSs describing the related subsystems.

radiation.name: radiation
radiation.description: Radiation emitted by the plasma and neutrals

real_time_data.name: real_time_data
real_time_data.description: Description of the data bus circulating on the real time data network of the machine. This is typically used (but not only) as an interface to the Plasma Control System (PCS)

reflectometer_profile.name: reflectometer_profile
reflectometer_profile.description: Profile reflectometer diagnostic. Multiple reflectometers are considered as independent diagnostics to be handled with different occurrence numbers

reflectometer_fluctuation.name: reflectometer_fluctuation
reflectometer_fluctuation.description: Fluctuation reflectometer diagnostic. Multiple reflectometers are considered as independent diagnostics to be handled with different occurrence numbers

sawteeth.name: sawteeth
sawteeth.description: Description of sawtooth events. This IDS must be used in homogeneous_time = 1 mode

spectrometer_uv.name: spectrometer_uv
spectrometer_uv.description: Spectrometer in uv light range diagnostic

spectrometer_visible.name: spectrometer_visible
spectrometer_visible.description: Spectrometer in visible light range diagnostic

summary.name: summary
summary.description: Summary of physics quantities from a simulation or an experiment. Dynamic quantities are either taken at given time slices (indicated in the "time" vector) or time-averaged over an interval (in such case the "time_width" of the interval is indicated and the "time" vector represents the end of each time interval).

temporary.name: temporary
temporary.description: Storage of undeclared data model components

transport_solver_numerics.name: transport_solver_numerics
transport_solver_numerics.description: Numerical quantities used by transport solvers and convergence details

wall.name: wall
wall.description: Description of the torus wall and its interaction with the plasma

waves.name: waves
waves.description: RF wave propagation and deposition. Note that current estimates in this IDS are a priori not taking into account synergies between multiple sources (a convergence loop with Fokker-Planck calculations is required to account for such synergies)

workflow.name: workflow
workflow.description: Description of the workflow that has produced this data entry. The workflow IDS can also be used to communicate information about workflow state between workflow components.
